comment:
* Defines the threshold value of the signal strength.
 * @hide

variables.name: SIGNAL_RSSI
variables.comment:
* Received Signal Strength Indication.
     * Range: -113 dBm and -51 dBm
     * Used RAN: GERAN, CDMA2000
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 27.007 section 8.5.

variables.name: SIGNAL_RSCP
variables.comment:
* Received Signal Code Power.
     * Range: -120 dBm to -25 dBm;
     * Used RAN: UTRAN
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 25.123, section 9.1.1.1

variables.name: SIGNAL_RSRP
variables.comment:
* Reference Signal Received Power.
     * Range: -140 dBm to -44 dBm;
     * Used RAN: EUTRAN
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 36.133 9.1.4

variables.name: SIGNAL_RSRQ
variables.comment:
* Reference Signal Received Quality
     * Range: -20 dB to -3 dB;
     * Used RAN: EUTRAN
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 36.133 9.1.7

variables.name: SIGNAL_RSSNR
SIGNAL_SSRSRP
variables.comment:
* 5G SS reference signal received power.
     * Range: -140 dBm to -44 dBm.
     * Used RAN: NGRAN
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 38.215.

variables.name: SIGNAL_SSRSRQ
variables.comment:
* 5G SS reference signal received quality.
     * Range: -20 dB to -3 dB.
     * Used RAN: NGRAN
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 38.215.

variables.name: SIGNAL_SSSINR
variables.comment:
* 5G SS signal-to-noise and interference ratio.
     * Range: -23 dB to 40 dB
     * Used RAN: NGRAN
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 38.215 section 5.1.*, 3GPP TS 38.133 section 10.1.16.1.

variables.name: mHysteresisMs
variables.comment:
* A hysteresis time in milliseconds to prevent flapping.
     * A value of 0 disables hysteresis

variables.name: mHysteresisDb
variables.comment:
* An interval in dB defining the required magnitude change between reports.
     * hysteresisDb must be smaller than the smallest threshold delta.
     * An interval value of 0 disables hysteresis.

variables.name: mThresholds
variables.comment:
* List of threshold values.
     * Range and unit must reference specific SignalMeasurementType
     * The threshold values for which to apply criteria.
     * A vector size of 0 disables the use of thresholds for reporting.

variables.name: mIsEnabled
variables.comment:
* {@code true} means modem must trigger the report based on the criteria;
     * {@code false} means modem must not trigger the report based on the criteria.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)
